## Cross-Domain Impact

@.understand-anything/reference-cross-domain-impact.json

## Quick Index (Code)

`reference-index.json` (~142 KB) — **jangan load seluruh file**. Targeted lookup:

- Grep: `rg "Enrollment" .understand-anything/reference-index.json`
- CLI: `node scripts/extract-graph.js --query classes --filter "Enrollment"`

## Entity → Code Mapping

`.understand-anything/reference-domain-to-code-mapper.json` — jika kosong, regenerate:

```bash
node scripts/create-domain-references.js
```

## Domain Query CLI

Full flows + `filePath` per step ada di `domain-graph.json`. Pakai:

```bash
node scripts/query-domain-code.js --domain "student-lifecycle" --list-steps
node scripts/query-domain-code.js --entity "Student" --show-impact
node scripts/query-domain-code.js --search "honor"
```

## Workflow

| Situasi | Langkah |
|---|---|
| Tambah fitur X | Domain → business rules → `filePath` dari steps |
| Bug di X | Domain → cross-domain impact → file terkait |
| Refactor sistem X | Affected flows → semua `filePath` → test plan |
| Apa yang break jika ubah X? | `reference-cross-domain-impact.json` + `--show-impact` |

## Quick Commands (untuk user)

- "Show me [domain] domain" → `reference-domain-index.json` atau `--domain`
- "What entities are in [flow]?" → `--domain ... --list-steps`
- "What code files for [entity]?" → `reference-domain-to-code-mapper.json` atau `--entity`
- "What's impacted by changing [X]?" → `reference-cross-domain-impact.json`
- "Where is [business rule] implemented?" → `filePath` di step flow (`domain-graph.json`)

## Stack (konteks)

- Laravel 11 ERP · 7 domain · 24 flows · 110 steps
- Coverage: 96% steps mapped ke `filePath`

## Token Efficiency

- Tanpa graph: ~50–75K tokens/query
- Dengan graph: ~5–15K tokens/query
- Hemat: **80–90%**

## Regenerate

Setelah update domain graph (`/understand-domain`):

